<subSubSection lastPageId="24" lastPageNumber="43" pageId="23" pageNumber="42" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="23.[812,1404,1359,1972]" pageId="23" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,981,1498,1522]" pageId="23" pageNumber="42">Adult habitus.</emphasis>
Biocellate. Head almost entirely dark brown but paired pale spots located over tentoria anterolateral to ocelli and at M‐ line; clypeus and area adjacent to lappets pale (
<figureCitation box="[1103,1184,1602,1626]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="24.[184,234,944,968]" captionTargetBox="[236,1405,212,922]" captionTargetId="figure-449@24.[656,878,321,687]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs. 78‐81. Neoperla zonata. 78. Head and pronotum, 79. Male terminalia, 80. Aedeagus, 81. Aedeagal sac, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4758896/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="42">Fig. 78</figureCitation>
). Pronotum brown with scattered, indistinct pale spots on disc. Wing membrane amber, veins brown except for costal margin. Hind femora banded with dark basal and apical bands; fore and mid femora and tibiae brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[812,1404,1359,1972]" pageId="23" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,879,1775,1799]" pageId="23" pageNumber="42">Male.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<quantity box="[1084,1166,1775,1799]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="23" pageNumber="42" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
. Process of tergum 7 rounded and spinulose around margin. Mesal sclerite of tergum 8 flat and bearing a few sensilla basiconica. Tergum 9 with sparse lateral sensilla patches on humps and a few scattered in mesal depression (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="24.[184,234,944,968]" captionTargetBox="[236,1405,212,922]" captionTargetId="figure-449@24.[656,878,321,687]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs. 78‐81. Neoperla zonata. 78. Head and pronotum, 79. Male terminalia, 80. Aedeagus, 81. Aedeagal sac, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4758896/files/figure.png" pageId="23" pageNumber="42">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
). Hemitergal processes long and slender.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758896" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4758896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4758896/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="43" startId="24.[184,234,944,968]" targetBox="[236,1405,212,922]" targetPageId="24">
<paragraph blockId="24.[184,1403,944,1002]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">
Figs. 78‐81. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stark &amp; Sivec" authorityYear="2008" box="[320,491,944,968]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonata">
<emphasis box="[320,491,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">Neoperla zonata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 78. Head and pronotum, 79. Male terminalia, 80. Aedeagus, 81. Aedeagal sac, ventral.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="24.[184,776,1082,1625]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">
Aedeagal tube plump and poorly sclerotized except on dorsum of basal half; apex of tube trilobed; lateral lobes sparsely armed with ca. 6 large spines on sides and with a cluster of smaller spines at tips (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="24.[184,234,944,968]" captionTargetBox="[236,1405,212,922]" captionTargetId="figure-449@24.[656,878,321,687]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="Figs. 78‐81. Neoperla zonata. 78. Head and pronotum, 79. Male terminalia, 80. Aedeagus, 81. Aedeagal sac, ventral." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4758896" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4758896/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">Figs. 80‐ 81</figureCitation>
); mesal lobe unarmed. Aedeagal sac not completely everted but about equal to tube in length and armed sparsely with small spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[184,776,1082,1625]" box="[184,404,1324,1348]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,276,1324,1348]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[184,776,1082,1625]" box="[184,385,1359,1383]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,257,1359,1382]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">Larva.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="43" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[184,776,1082,1625]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,318,1394,1418]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name refers to the banding pattern on the hind femora.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="43" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[184,776,1082,1625]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[184,309,1463,1487]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The aedeagus and external genitalia of this species is of the general 
<typeStatus box="[502,553,1498,1522]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">type</typeStatus>
seen in 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivec &amp; Zwick" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Zwick" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanica">
<emphasis box="[642,775,1499,1522]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">N. taiwanica</emphasis>
Sivec &amp; Zwick
</taxonomicName>
but the lateral aedeagal lobes in that species are much smaller than those found in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Sivec &amp; Zwick 1987)" baseAuthorityName="Sivec &amp; Zwick" baseAuthorityYear="1987" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Neoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zonata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="43">N. zonata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; P. Zwick" box="[267,495,1601,1625]" pageId="24" pageNumber="43" pagination="391 - 405" refId="ref16652" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; P. Zwick. 1987. Some Neoperla from Taiwan (Plecoptera: Perlidae). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 37: 391 - 405." type="journal article" year="1987">Sivec &amp; Zwick 1987</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
